.TH MPI_Get_count 3 "9/20/2012" " " "MPI"
.SH NAME
MPI_Get_count \-  Gets the number of "top level" elements 
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
int MPI_Get_count( MPICH2_CONST MPI_Status *status, MPI_Datatype datatype, int *count )
.fi
.SH INPUT PARAMETERS
.PD 0
.TP
.B status 
- return status of receive operation (Status) 
.PD 1
.PD 0
.TP
.B datatype 
- datatype of each receive buffer element (handle) 
.PD 1

.SH OUTPUT PARAMETER
.PD 0
.TP
.B count 
- number of received elements (integer) 
Notes:
If the size of the datatype is zero, this routine will return a count of
zero.  If the amount of data in 
.I status
is not an exact multiple of the 
size of 
.I datatype
(so that 
.I count
would not be integral), a 
.I count
of
.I MPI_UNDEFINED
is returned instead.
.PD 1

.SH NOTES FOR FORTRAN
All MPI routines in Fortran (except for 
.I MPI_WTIME
and 
.I MPI_WTICK
) have
an additional argument 
.I ierr
